    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Park System Installation</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using clean automatic transmission fluid to hold the bearing or bushing in place, install
                the output shaft bearing for slip yoke models and the bushing for fixed yoke models.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010156" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0065844.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Be careful when installing the output shaft not to damage the seals.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the output shaft was removed, install the output shaft and park gear assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010157" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0065841.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the park pawl shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010158" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018722.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the park pawl shaft.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the park pawl.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the park pawl return spring.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the parking rod guide plate and bolts.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 25 Nm (18 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010159" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0058022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new extension housing gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010160" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0056155.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the extension housing and the 9 bolts.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 47 Nm (35 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010161" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0056161.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tool, install the output shaft nut.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 200 Nm (148 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010162" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018709.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the OSS sensor electrical connector.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010163" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0055907.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower the transmission onto the rear mount and install the bolts.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 94 Nm (69 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010164" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0056159.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the output shaft flange and a new bolt.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 135 Nm (100 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010165" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018715.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear driveshaft. For additional information, refer to
                <exhotlnk document="../S06/S06002.htm" bookname="S06002">Driveshaft in S06002</exhotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start the engine. Move the transmission range selector lever through all the gear ranges,
                checking for engagements.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>The use of any other transmission fluid than specified can result in the transmission failing to
                    operate in a normal manner or transmission failure.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the vehicle in NEUTRAL, engine running and the transmission at normal operating
                temperature 66-77&#176;C (150-170&#176;F), check and adjust the transmission fluid level and check for
                any leaks. If fluid is needed, add fluid in increments of 0.24 liter (0.5 pint) until the correct level
                is achieved (fluid should be in the cross-hatched area of the fluid level indicator).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
